snippet.textDisplay: As a physicist I'd like to tag in here - the claims are all marketing. "Inertia generators" aren't a thing. Any weight would be identical, and adding weight isn't particularly hard to do. The aerodynamics are actually disappointing. There are a few aspects which look mildly interesting, but to be honest all companies are working far too much on trash which doesn't work (recall vortex generators) than on actually effective aerodynamics. There is still a fair amount of improvements which can go into the aerodynamics, but the fact that nobody is making an ugly club with perfect aero suggests that aero makes very little difference or they would have let the results do the talking. Bottom line is its all marketing, in fact any time you see a buzz word you can completely ignore the claim. "Inertia generators" to describe a weight, I mean come on.
